the step with cloudformation outputs

properties.description: nil when no stack exists

options.name: PROGRESS
options.description: Progressing well, no errors, no rollback

options.name: ROLLING_BACK
options.description: Rolling back to previous version or deleting on create failure

options.name: CREATE_FAILED
options.description: Create failure, rolled back to nothing

options.name: ROLLED_BACK
options.description:
Update failure, rolled back to previous version and now stable.
Good when waiting, bad when updating or scaling.

options.name: MISSING
options.description:
Missing, not present currently, either never created or deleted, not not
'rolled back'

properties.name: infraOutputStepId
properties.description:
the step with cloudformation outputs
containing the secret ARN

options.name: UNAVAILABLE
options.description: Progressing well, no errors, no rollback

options.name: EXECUTION
options.description:
Plan has been executed, and is either executing, completed or failed,
either way, the stack itself now has the status.

properties.name: quickMode
properties.description: Skips scale up/down, directly applying the updates in one infra call.

properties.name: rotateCredentials
properties.description: Rotates database credentials

object.name: DeploymentEventType_StackWait
object.description: Waits for the stack to be ready, without making any changes

properties.name: request
properties.description: when set, publishes deployment events back to the requester

properties.name: tag
properties.description:
Defaults to the full git hash being deployed (or passed in --version
parameter)

properties.name: registry
properties.description: Defaults to the environment's registry, set here to override

properties.name: readPermission
properties.description:
This application is allowed to read from the
bucket. Default is true unless write_permission is true.

properties.name: writePermission
properties.description:
This application is allowed to write to the bucket. Does not imply
read_permissions. Default is false.

properties.name: application
properties.description: `application.name` for an app in the same environment

properties.name: bucketName
properties.description:
Full name of the 'bucket' for the blobstore,
does not follow any patterns.

properties.name: replayChance
properties.description: chance percentage of sidecar behavior: replay message or process then treat as a deadletter

properties.name: noDeadletters
properties.description:
if true, sidecar will not send dead letter messages, should only be used
for dead-letter handlers (e.g. dante)

properties.name: prefix
properties.description: Default is not to filter, but requires the route_group to be FALLBACK

properties.name: targetContainer
properties.description: Default: first defined container

properties.name: bypassIngress
properties.description: Default: false

properties.name: port
properties.description: Default: 8080

properties.name: routeGroup
properties.description: Default: NORMAL

properties.name: targetContainer
properties.description: Default: first defined container

properties.name: port
properties.description: Default: 8080

properties.name: grpcMethod
properties.description:
Baz in the method /foo.bar.v1.FooBar/Baz
Subscribes only to the method, if not set, subscribes to all methods

properties.name: replyTo
properties.description: For request-reply replies, filters to the reply.reply_to field

properties.name: rawMessage
properties.description:
The payload is not the standard messaging payload
It should be parsed into a o5.messaging.v1.topic.RawMessage
Used for infrastructure messages, e.g. AWS EventBridge or CloudWatch events.
Setting non_grpc in AWS will set 'rawMessageDelivery' to *false*, i.e., the SNS wrapper
will be included.

properties.name: metaInfraEvents
properties.description:
Subscribes to infra events, e.g. AWS ECS Task status
Requires grant_meta_deploy_permissions to be true

options.name: ADAPTER_ENDPOINT
options.description: address of the sidecar / adapter for gRPC dial

properties.name: s3Direct
properties.description:
Sets the variable as s3://<bucket>/<?sub_path>
TODO: Deprecate this and build a wrapper through the sidecar

properties.name: databaseName
properties.description: references a database in the top level array

properties.name: quickMode
properties.description:
Migrates the stack in one single call, not compatible with database
migration

properties.name: name
properties.description: Topology topology = 2;

properties.name: directIngress
properties.description:
When true, HTTP and gRPC requests will be routed directly to the runtime
container, not via the ingress sidecar. The runtime container is
responsible for all security, throttling etc.

properties.name: principal
properties.description: This is a lookup in the env file

properties.name: ref
properties.description:
The blobstore is a reference to a one owned by another application, it will
not be created in the stack for the current application, but permissions
will be granted.

properties.name: dbName
properties.description:
The name of the database within the postgres instance, default is the
name in the parent message

properties.name: serverGroup
properties.description:
default is 'default' - identifies which database server from the
environment config this belongs with

properties.name: demand
properties.description: The amount of Memory and CPU to allocate to the container

properties.name: mountDockerSocket
properties.description: gives access to /var/run/docker.sock in the container

properties.name: hostHeader
properties.description:
when set, adds a host header rule to all listener rules. For routes with
specified subdomains, the subdomain value is added as a prefix to this
value.
This allows re-use of the same listener for multiple (related) environments.

properties.name: lookupName
properties.description: used to match in application configs

properties.name: o5DeployerAssumeRole
properties.description: The role to assume when deploying to this environment

properties.name: sidecarImageVersion
properties.description: Must be set, no default.

properties.name: sidecarImageRepo
properties.description: defaults to ghcr.io/pentops/o5-runtime-sidecar

properties.name: globalNamespace
properties.description:
S3 buckets (and others?) must be globally unique for all AWS accounts and regions,
buckets are named {name}-{app}-{environment}-{region}-{global_namespace}

properties.name: name
properties.description: lookup val used in o5.application.v1.Runtime.named_env_policies
